1	/**
2	 * CountStrike — count-strike numbers (DIRECTION "CountStrike").
3	 *
4	 * The DOM ships the FINAL formatted value (SEO / no-JS safe). On the motion
5	 * tier a once ScrollTrigger (start "top 80%") rewinds the text to `from`, then
6	 * tweens a plain counter object to `to` over `duration` (EASE.SETTLE), writing
7	 * el.textContent = fmt(value) each frame from a cached element + cached
8	 * formatter (created once, never per frame). Holds forever (once:true).
9	 * Supersedes the legacy CountUp.jsx (left untouched/dead).
10	 *
11	 * Props:
12	 *   to        number  (required) target value.
13	 *   from      number  0          start value.
14	 *   decimals  number  0          fraction digits (min == max).
15	 *   prefix    string  ""         prepended to the formatted number.
16	 *   suffix    string  ""         appended to the formatted number.
17	 *   duration  number  DUR.SCENE  tween length (seconds).
18	 *   format    fn      —          optional n=>string override of the formatter.
19	 *   className string  ""         passthrough (caller adds font-mono as desired).
20	 *   as        string  "span"     rendered tag.
21	 *
22	 * Default formatter: en-IN grouping so 241800 → "2,41,800".
23	 * The accessible name is the element's real text (the DOM ships the final
24	 * formatted value; no aria-label — spans may not carry one, axe aria-prohibited-attr).
25	 * Root: data-count-strike, tabular-nums.
26	 *
27	 * Gate (scar #8): useMotionStatic() ⇒ final value stays as rendered,
28	 * data-static="true" + data-struck="true", zero GSAP.
29	 *
